Defendant David A Robertson in court with attorney Torrie R. Williams.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS  in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to each other; STRAIGHT TIME; NO ELECTRONIC MONITORING.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 24 MONTHS.
AS TO BOTH COUNTS:
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Letter of apology to Tom X.;
*  No contact with Tom X.;
*  Maintain full time employment/school or a combination of both;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

AS TO COUNT 1 ONLY:
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $1140.00 to Tom X. or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Perform 20 hours of community service.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
